10 c. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall
11 verify the full-time employment status of the
12 student's parent(s) prior to a student who qualifies
13 pursuant to this paragraph receiving any Oklahoma
14 Higher Learning Access Program benefit award.
15 d. For the purposes of this paragraph, "certified
16 classroom teacher" means a certified, full-time
17 classroom teacher who has been employed as a teacher
18 in a public school district classroom in this state
19 for a minimum of ten (10) years prior to his or her
20 child applying for participation in the program. The
21 teacher is not required to have been employed by the
22 same public school district for ten (10) consecutive
23 years. Certified classroom teacher does not mean a
24 certified teacher who is employed as a school district
Req. No. 14152 Page 12

1 superintendent, principal, or any other position
2 within the administration of a public school district
3 when his or her child applies for participation in the
4 program or prior to his or her child receiving any
5 Oklahoma Higher Learning Access Program benefit award.
6 F. The financial qualification of a student as set forth in
7 subsections D and E of this section shall be certified by the
8 contact person or by the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education
9 on the agreement form provided by the Oklahoma State Regents for
10 Higher Education. The form shall be retained in the permanent
11 record of the student and a copy forwarded to the Oklahoma State
12 Regents for Higher Education.
13 G. Agreements shall be witnessed by the parent, custodial
14 parent, or guardian of the student, who shall further agree to:
15 1. Assist the student in achieving compliance with the
16 agreements;
17 2. Confer, when requested to do so, with the school contact
18 person, other school personnel, and program mentors;
19 3. Provide information requested by the Oklahoma State Regents
20 for Higher Education or the State Board of Education; and
21 4. Assist the student in completing forms and reports required
22 for program participation, making applications to institutions and
23 schools of higher learning, and filing applications for student
24 grants and scholarships.
Req. No. 14152 Page 13

1 H. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall
2 promulgate rules for the determination of student compliance with
3 agreements made pursuant to this section.
4 I. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall
5 designate personnel to coordinate tracking of program records for
6 the years when students participating in the program are still in
7 the schools or are being educated by other means, provide staff
8 development for contact persons in the schools, and provide liaison
9 with the State Board of Education and local organizations and
10 individuals participating in the program.
11 J. The school district where an Oklahoma Higher Learning Access
12 Program student is enrolled when the student begins participation in
13 the program and any subsequent school district where the student
14 enrolls shall forward information regarding participation by the
15 student in the program to a school to which the student transfers
16 upon the request of the school for the records of the student.
17 K. Students participating in the Oklahoma Higher Learning
18 Access Program shall provide their Social Security number or their
19 student identification number used by their school to the Oklahoma
20 State Regents for Higher Education. The State Regents shall keep
21 the numbers confidential and use them only for administrative
22 purposes.
23 L. The State Regents may provide an exception to the age limits
24 provided for in paragraphs 1 and 2 of subsection C of this section
Req. No. 14152 Page 14

1 to a student due to hardship circumstances and allow an application
2 to the Oklahoma Higher Learning Access Program for twelfth-grade
3 students enrolled in a public or private school and students who are
4 educated by other means and are in the equivalent of twelfth grade.
5 Provided, however, the exception due to hardship circumstances shall
6 not apply to:
7 1. A student enrolled in a public or private school after the
8 student's official date of high school graduation;
9 2. A student educated by other means who is age nineteen (19)
10 or older; or
11 3. Any student who is age twenty-one (21) or older.
12 The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall promulgate
13 rules to implement the provisions of this subsection.
14 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
15 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
16 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
17 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
